description:
&lt;p&gt;We are delighted to be able to recruit to Administrative assistant to work within the Microbiology department of the Royal Devon and Exeter NHS Foundation Trust.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Microbiology Department at the Royal Devon and Exeter NHS Foundation Trust is part of the Pathology service providing a diagnostic Microbiology service to the Trust and community. This forward thinking hospital is situated on the edge of Dartmoor in the city of Exeter with easy access to the M5 corridor and excellent transport links to the open countryside and Devon coastline. There is an on-site restaurant, crèche facilities and a choice of coffee/tea outlets. The laboratory has its own rest area within the department.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen to join our covid-19 testing team. As part of the team you will be working in a busy high throughput environment.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Your role will be to provide administrative support to the covid-19 testing service in the Molecular Department based in the Old Pathology Building.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The duties will include the following:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Receipt of pathology samples prior to analysis.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Inputting of data form patient request forms into the computer&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Dealing with patient result enquiries via the telephone.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;The post will also involve a number of general laboratory duties as dictated by the Laboratory.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful applicant will possess good keyboard skills, an excellent telephone manner and should be highly literate and numerate. They must be capable of working as part of a team, having good communications skills, with an appreciation of the Hospital environment being an advantage.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Hours: The post is for 37.5 hours per week which will be required to be worked over a variety of shift patterns from 07.00 – 22.00, 7 days a week. This is a &lt;strong&gt;Fixed Term contract &lt;/strong&gt;for a period of 12 months.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If further information or a laboratory visit is required please contact Michele Heritage on 01392 402908.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our vision is to provide safe, high quality seamless services delivered with courtesy and respect. To achieve our vision we expect all our staff to uphold our Trust values. Our Trust values are:&lt;br /&gt; Honesty, Openness &amp; Integrity&lt;br /&gt; Fairness&lt;br /&gt; Inclusion &amp; Collaboration&lt;br /&gt; Respect &amp; Dignity&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;***Preference will be given to staff with ‘Priority’ and &#39;At Risk&#39; status including NHS At Risk staff throughout Devon.***&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;DUE TO THE ANTICIPATED HIGH NUMBER OF APPLICATIONS FOR THIS POST WE RESERVE THE RIGHT TO CLOSE THE VACANCY BEFORE THE CLOSING DATE.&lt;/p&gt;
